## Dependencies & Risks

### Critical Path Dependencies

1. **Story #16 (Automated scraper)** must complete **by Day 3** before:
   - Story #17 (Error logging) can be tested
   - Story #18 (Retry logic) can be implemented

2. **Story #3 (Render deployment)** should complete **by Day 4** to enable:
   - End-to-end testing in staging environment
   - Stakeholder demos of deployed application

3. **Story #9 (Dietary filters)** should complete **by Day 3** before:
   - Story #12 (Empty state) can be fully tested with filter combinations

### Identified Risks

| Risk | Probability | Impact | Mitigation Strategy | Owner |
|------|-------------|--------|---------------------|-------|
| Render deployment complexity underestimated | Medium | High | Allocate Louis + Sachit pairing; research Render docs before starting; budget extra 2-3 hours | Louis |
| Scraper cron job (8 pts) is largest story | Medium | Medium | Break into subtasks; daily check-ins on progress; Louis prioritizes this early in sprint | Louis |
| Thanksgiving week approaching (Nov 21-24) | High | Medium | Complete all critical work by Nov 19; avoid carrying over high-risk items | Team |
| Mobile responsive design may uncover edge cases | Medium | Low | Piquet to test on multiple devices (iPhone, Android, tablet); iterate quickly | Piquet |
| Empty state depends on filter implementation | Low | Low | Parm completes filters by Day 3; Piquet begins empty state Day 4 | Parm/Piquet |

### Assumptions
- Yale Dining website HTML structure remains stable (scraper won't break)
- Render free tier has sufficient capacity for staging deployment
- No major stakeholder requirement changes mid-sprint
- Team members have 20 hours/week availability as planned

---

## Definition of Done (Sprint 3)

For each user story to be marked "Done":

**Code Quality:**
- [ ] All acceptance criteria met and manually verified
- [ ] Code merged to `develop` branch via pull request
- [ ] Minimum 1 code review approval (Louis reviews all PRs)
- [ ] No merge conflicts with `develop`

**Testing:**
- [ ] Manual testing completed by developer in local environment
- [ ] Manual QA completed by different team member in staging
- [ ] Mobile responsive testing on iPhone and Android devices (for UI stories)

**Deployment:**
- [ ] Feature deployed to staging environment
- [ ] Staging deployment verified working (no 500 errors)
- [ ] No critical or high-severity bugs blocking user testing

**Documentation:**
- [ ] README updated if setup instructions changed
- [ ] Inline code comments for complex logic
- [ ] Django admin registered for new models

**Product Owner Acceptance:**
- [ ] Piquet has reviewed and accepted the work

