## Sprint Backlog Task Breakdown (Example)

### Story #9: Implement dietary preference filters (5 points)

**Tasks:**
- [ ] Create filter button UI with Tailwind CSS (Breakfast/Lunch/Dinner) - 2 hours
- [ ] Add dietary tag checkboxes (Vegan, Vegetarian, Gluten-Free, Halal) - 2 hours
- [ ] Implement Django view filtering logic based on dietary tags - 3 hours
- [ ] Connect frontend buttons to backend filter endpoints - 2 hours
- [ ] Test filter combinations (e.g., Vegan + Lunch) - 1 hour
- [ ] Style active filter states (blue highlight) - 1 hour
- [ ] Add "Clear all filters" button - 1 hour
- [ ] Code review and merge - 1 hour

**Total Estimated Hours:** 13 hours (~5 story points at 2.5 hours/point)

---

## Notes from Planning Session

**Key Decisions:**
- Prioritized deployment (Story #3) early to unblock staging testing
- Louis to focus exclusively on scraper (Story #16) as it's the largest/riskiest story
- Piquet will handle all UI polish stories (#10, #12, #14) for design consistency
- Team agreed to drop Story #11 (dish count) if time runs short - lowest priority

**Open Questions:**
- Do we need CAPTCHA on reactions? (Deferred to Sprint 4 discussion)
- Should we use Google Analytics or Plausible? (Kyle to advise)

**Team Confidence Level:** 7/10
- Confident in filtering and UI stories
- Moderate concern about Render deployment complexity
- High confidence in scraper implementation (Louis has experience)

